                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"jobs\"\u003eJobs\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOpportunities for specific jobs in the Civil Service and central government organisations can be found on \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"http://bit.ly/GiG_CSjobs\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCivil Service jobs\u003c/a\u003e. You can search specifically for Geography jobs by selecting ‘Geography’ from the “Job Role” drop down list.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIndividual organisations in the wider public sector advertise opportunities on their websites:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.ordnancesurvey.co.uk/careers\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eOrdnance Survey\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://environmentagencyjobs.tal.net/candidate/jobboard/vacancy/1/adv\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eEnvironment Agency\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.gov.scot/about/contact-information/jobs-vacancies/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eScottish Government\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.sepa.org.uk/jobs/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eScottish Environment Protection Agency\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://cymru-wales.tal.net/candidate/jobboard/vacancy/5/adv\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eWelsh Government\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://naturalresources.wales/about-us/jobs-and-placements/?lang=en\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eNatural Resources Wales\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nao.org.uk/careers/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eNational Audit Office\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eIndividual Local Authorities\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn addition to applying for specific roles as set out above, it is also possible to enter through an apprenticeship, graduate entry programme or profession specific recruitment. Whilst there is no apprenticeship or graduate entry programme for the geography profession yet, a number of our members enter through one of the entry routes for one of the other professions in the Government \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"http://bit.ly/GiG_AF\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eAnalysis Function\u003c/a\u003e of which the geography profession is part or through the generalist fast stream and then join the geography profession once they take up post (a number of our members are members of two professions e.g. economic geographers of spatial statisticians):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.faststream.gov.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eFast stream\u003c/a\u003e, including some internships and apprenticeships opportunities for all professions as well as \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.faststream.gov.uk/science-engineering/index.html\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Science and Engineering\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://gss.civilservice.gov.uk/careers/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Statistical Service\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service-government-economic-service\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Economic Service\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service-government-social-research-profession\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Social Research\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.operational-research.gov.uk/recruitment/gateway/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Operational Research Service\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://governmentscienceandengineering.blog.gov.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Science and Engineering\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/digital-data-and-technology-profession\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eDigital, Data and Technology Profession\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-actuarys-department/about/recruitment#who-we-look-for\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Actuaries Department\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"government-geography-profession\"\u003eGovernment Geography Profession\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Government Geography Profession welcomes members from UK Civil Servants, Crown Servants and Public Servants covering a wide range of organisations from Ministerial departments to the Ordnance Survey, Environment Agency and local authorities. If you are not sure whether you are a civil, crown or public servant please consult your HR department.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor existing members of the Government Geography Profession we will advertise available positions on the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://app.slack.com/client/TBGEB8082/CBGJPJPBP\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGeography Profession Slack channel\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you are a civil, crown or public servant, and a geographer, find out more about our \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/professional-benefits\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ebenefits\u003c/a\u003e and how to \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://members.geography.gov.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ejoin us\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"contact-us\"\u003eContact us\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor more information please contact us on \u003ca href=\"mailto:GovHeadGeog@defra.gov.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovHeadGeog@defra.gov.uk \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
